				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Anduran the Artisan wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Why even bother with a mana drain recourse? You're thinking about things the hard way.
<br />

<br />
Just have a flat line mana cost and a flat line buff duration for the pet.
<br />

<br />
Damage Modifier of say... 100 %
<br />
Increase Current HP by 5000
<br />
Increase Total HP by 5000
<br />
Cannot parse melee mitigation (go lucy go!) let say a 15 % damage shaved off.
<br />
Add Proc (750DD, 5 hit calliav component- think prism strike/skin but where strike does damage and skin is more than one hit)
<br />

<br />
Allowed Targets: Pet
<br />
Duration: 15 ticks
<br />
Mana Cost: 3000
<br />

<br />
15 ticks so 1.5 minutes, assuming your pet normally does 100 DPS, it's now doing 200, meaning a bonus 9000 melee damage, slightly better tanking ability, as well as (assuming 2 PPM main hand 1 PPM off hand) another 4.5 procs @ 750 a pop, makes for 12375 damage added on top of base pet.  
<br />

<br />
Now, 3000 mana is a lot of freaking mana, so it's gonna be a 1-2 shot trick for most, however, that said, we'd be able to generate a lot better burst DPS without overstepping the mark too hard in long term DPS, simply because something like this could not be sustained.
<br />

<br />
This would help with soloability as well, if you cast this on your pet, you're looking at generally getting 4.5 x 5 hit calliavs as well as what... 2? maybe 3 prism strikes, meaning 25 hits negated, as well as having 5000 more hp stacked on top, meaning you'd be able to solo some stuff, at the expense of a large proportion of mana.  This would be good.
<br />

<br />
I dunno, something like this has been brought up and debated a lot, and I have no idea why it's not implemented at least in some fashion, a way to do damage through our pets rather than as basically a hybrid wizard that we are now.
<br />

<br />
Something like this wouldn't have to go in at the same specifications, or even close, maybe it'd be a 300 mana spell and have about 1/15th the effect, who knows, but something ALONG these lines would be incredibly good for versatility.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

