				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem that I can see with your idea Anduran, is that it (like our pets at the moment) doesn't scale well. Sure, 3k is a drop in the bucket when you have ~8k base mana pool, but the problem with pet and raids starts pretty much when a Mage starts raiding. Even for me with a 6kish mana pool raiding would instantly have my mana pool cut in half, leaving me less mana to nuke (Yes, on some fights I find that I can burn nearly all of my mana pool.)
<br />

<br />
There would need to be some scaling in the mana cost/outpur of the buff, and besides different spells (/shudder) dropping in different zones I am not sure how this could be done. Having focus items add better stats and abilities, as well as reviewing the itemization of them, might be a bit better for making pet damage scale. However if the problem is the idea that mana in must account for damage out, I just don't see it. Melee has always been "free" so to speak, so why would we be the exception that changes the schema? Because afterall (with that line of thinking) isn't a Rogue dagger just a "free" DoT?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=256883&resize=true"target="_new"><img src="http://members.cox.net/stoneshaper/zarnameplate.gif"border="0"></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
